Theodore Kaczynski, 54, was arrested in Montana and faces the death penalty for the California bombings.
His lawyers seek a single trial for all charges.
His family was informed of the decision to seek the death penalty.
Kaczynski has pleaded not guilty to all charges.
The trial is set for November 12 in Sacramento.
Juror identities will be kept secret, with nearly 600 prospects being interviewed.
Legal experts believe Kaczynski's mental health may be his best defense.
